<h2>Solar Incentives in Anaheim</h2>
<p>Anaheim residents can take advantage of multiple solar incentives that significantly reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost, including equipment and installation, through 2032. This credit drops to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034 before expiring for residential installations. California offers additional state-level incentives, including the Self-Generation Incentive Program (SGIP) for battery storage systems, which can provide rebates up to \$1,000 per kWh of storage capacity. SCE customers may also qualify for specific utility rebates and time-of-use rate structures that maximize solar savings. Property tax exemptions ensure that adding solar panels won't increase your property tax assessment, while the increased home value from solar installation remains tax-free.</p>

