<p>When selecting a solar installer in Anaheim, prioritize companies with proper California Contractors State License Board (CSLB) licensing, specifically C-46 Solar classification. Look for installers with extensive local experience in Orange County, as they understand SCE's interconnection requirements and local permitting processes. Top-tier companies offer comprehensive warranties covering panels (25 years), inverters (10-25 years), and workmanship (10-25 years). Verify certifications from the North American Board of Certified Energy Practitioners (NABCEP) and check Better Business Bureau ratings. Request multiple quotes and ensure each proposal includes detailed production estimates based on your specific roof conditions and shading analysis. Reputable installers will handle all permits, SCE interconnection paperwork, and provide ongoing system monitoring. Avoid door-to-door sales tactics and companies requiring large upfront payments before work begins.</p>

